Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

; Disables the Windows Troubleshooting Service — stops automatic diagnostic scans and data collection sent to Microsoft.
; It automatically detects known issues on your system and applies fixes sourced from Microsoft servers, without any user action.
; In practice it runs background scans, contacts Microsoft, and can silently change system settings.
; No real benefit for an experienced user who manages their own system.

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\TroubleshootingSvc]
"Start"=dword:00000004
